snippet.textDisplay: Man I never do these comment things I’m hardly even on YouTube. But I really felt this. I just wanted to say that you’ve got this mama. I was in your same position just last year in the beginning and even through most of my pregnancy as far as the emotions go and feeling like you’re stressing your baby. I wasn’t with my baby’s father it was very unexpected. I hadn’t really been in any relationships even before my pregnancy. I was always single, and like you, i spent A LOT of time and love on my nephew. So I put a lot of guilt on myself for many reasons which I’m sure you have too. Even though I knew that it was a blessing in disguise. But just know those feelings are normal. Let them come and let them go and just remember to breath & after every breakdown/meltdown talk to your baby about something happy, eat something good, laugh at something funny, hug your mom..etc. It’s the little things that really go a long way. Youre going to feel so many emotions but growing a whole ass human being and if that doesn’t make someone emotional idk what does lol & You’re such an amazing woman and you’re going to be an even more amazing mom. & if there is one thing I wish people would have told me more during my pregnancy it is that that little baby loves you sooooooo much already. Props to you for posting this because I could only imagine. Lol sending you soooo much love!!
